TextBody:
Hi Leonardo,

Please find below the Server Offline Patches.

Before upgrading the EPP server we strongly recommend creating a Snapshot of the EPP server from the VM/AWS/Azure/GCP, where the server is hosted.

Please go to Dashboard -> Live Update -> Offline patch uploader.
 
Please select Choose File -> Select the patch file 5.9.0.0 -> Upload Patch. Please wait a few moments after pressing Upload Patch and you should receive a green message on the top of the page that the upload was successful. You can track the progress of the installation in Dashboard -> Live Update(it takes about 5 - 10 minutes per patch).

Please repeat the steps for each EPP server version upgrade and in order: 5.9.0.0 -> 5.9.1.0 -> 5.9.2.0 -> 5.9.3.0. -> Vulnerability Patch.

Download links:
EPP5900 offline patch: https://download.endpointprotector.com/offline_patches/EPP500615900.tar.gz

EPP5910 offline patch: https://download.endpointprotector.com/offline_patches/EPP500625910.tar.gz

EPP5920 offline patch: https://download.endpointprotector.com/offline_patches/EPP500635920.tar.gz

EPP5930 offline patch: https://download.endpointprotector.com/offline_patches/EPP500645930.tar.gz

Vulnerability patch(please apply after upgrading to 5.9.3.0): https://download.endpointprotector.com/offline_patches/MP-HWA-EPP4-U8800.tar.gz

Please let me know if there is any other information that I can provide, or if you would like us to schedule a remote session and do the steps together.

Best Regards,
Flaviu Moldovan | Technical Support Engineer
Endpoint Protector by CoSoSys, now part of Netwrix
DLP | Device Control | Content Aware Protection | eDiscovery | Enforced Encryption
www.endpointprotector.com
